  <refnamediv>
    <refname>loc</refname>
    <refpurpose>Access a group of rows and columns by label(s) or a boolean array.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Syntax</title>
   <synopsis>
   dfr.loc(input_string,df_name)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>input_string :</term>
            <listitem><para> String containing the input labels/conditions</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>df_name :</term>
            <listitem><para> String containing the DataFrame name</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>Returns :</term>
            <listitem><para> dframefunc instance output</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
.loc[] is primarily label based, but may also be used with a boolean array.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
// Getting the data of passengers who survived
dfr.loc("dfr.Survived==1","dfr")

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

